description:
Extend note functionality to track whether notes came from agent or human:

```bash
# Agent note (default)
tk note abc123 "PR ready: github.com/..."

# Human note (feedback, answers)
tk note abc123 "Use Stripe for payments" --from human
```

In ticks client, update AddNote to support author:
```go
func (c *Client) AddNote(taskID string, content string, opts ...string) error {
    args := []string{"note", taskID, content}
    args = append(args, opts...)  // e.g., "--from", "human"
    return c.runCommand(args...)
}

// Convenience methods
func (c *Client) AddAgentNote(taskID, content string) error {
    return c.AddNote(taskID, content)
}

func (c *Client) AddHumanNote(taskID, content string) error {
    return c.AddNote(taskID, content, "--from", "human")
}
```

This helps distinguish note sources for the agent when reading feedback.

Acceptance criteria:
- [ ] --from flag supported on tk note
- [ ] AddHumanNote convenience method added
- [ ] Notes stored with author metadata
- [ ] Can filter notes by author when reading
